headline: The Latest Global Commodities News
summary: It makes it seven out of the past eight days that most-active hogs end lower, with  CME  hogs exposed to the negative effects of tariffs being levied on Mexico and Canada both.  Mexico, in particular, is the largest buyer of U.S. pork.  If it stays on the chopping block for tariffs, then that may put significant stress on the futures contract.
